-- South African Province Curbs Meat Amid Disease Fears, Business Day Reports
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2010-10-12T04:52:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/south-african-province-restricts-meat-over-disease-business-day-reports.html
South African placed restrictions on
the transfer of meat products or animals within the Greater
Tubatse municipality in Limpopo province after a suspected
outbreak of foot-and-mouth disease, Business Day reported.  The Johannesburg-based newspaper cited the State Veterinary
Authorities.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  